<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFF8FFC7FF71F9ADFF1DF8E3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71F9ADFD95F937" blockId="16.[151,1437,1626,1869]" box="[151,616,1663,1689]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFF8FFC7FF79F9ADFF14F937" box="[159,233,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1923,1947]" captionTargetBox="[217,1371,196,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-32@62.[206,1381,181,1899]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 9. Eudocima materna group and African Eudocima adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605516/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 9</figureCitation>
: I–J, 19: E, 24: R–T, 31: C, 92: E)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71F971FF1DF8E3" blockId="16.[151,1437,1626,1869]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This is the only African 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FE4EF971FDE7F913" box="[424,538,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FE4EF971FDE7F913" box="[424,538,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with no hindwing medial patch. The hindwing has a broad continuous marginal band similar to the one found in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FDECF915FD61F94F" box="[522,668,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridescens">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FDECF915FD61F94F" box="[522,668,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. iridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the Australian region; however, the female of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FB2FF915FAA6F94F" box="[1225,1371,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridescens">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FB2FF915FAA6F94F" box="[1225,1371,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. iridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a green forewing transverse band. The male of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FD71F939FCEBF8AB" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[663,790,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divitiosa">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FD71F939FCEBF8AB" box="[663,790,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. divitiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a unique pale greenish band bordering the distal side of the PM line. It has been recorded from numerous localities throughout subsaharan Africa (De Prins &amp; De Prins 2022).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
